## The Verdict Hierarchy: 6 Verdicts (v38.2)

| Verdict | Symbol | Meaning | Memory Route | User Sees |
|---------|--------|---------|--------------|-----------|
| **SEAL** | âœ“ | All 9 floors green. Safe. | LEDGER + ACTIVE | Returns response |
| **PARTIAL** | âš ï¸ | 1-2 minor floors breached. Acceptable with warning. | PHOENIX + LEDGER | Response + warning |
| **SABAR** | â¹ï¸ | Major breach. System pauses to cool down. | LEDGER + ACTIVE | "[SABAR] Let me reconsider..." |
| **VOID** | âœ— | Critical floor breach. Output rejected. | VOID only (never canonical) | "[VOID] I cannot output this." |
| **888_HOLD** | â¸ï¸ | Ambiguous edge case. Escalate to human. | LEDGER | "Awaiting human review..." |
| **SUNSET** | ğŸŒ… | Truth expired. Revoke sealed memory. | LEDGER â†’ PHOENIX | Revocation logged |

**SABAR = The Constitutional Pause.** When multiple floors breach or entropy spikes, the system pauses rather than forcing a bad output. It cools, reflects, tries again.

**SUNSET = Lawful Revocation (v38.2).** When external reality changes, previously sealed truths can be revoked and sent back to PHOENIX for re-trial.

